 the organization; and that the FBI first underestimated Weather's seriousness, then overestimated its effectiveness, and how Weather outwitted them. Eckstein reveals how an obsessed and panicked President Nixon and his inner circle sought to bypass a cautious J. Edgar Hoover, contributing to the creation of the rogue Plumbers Unit that eventually led to Watergate.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Apr 2020) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / Radicalism.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300224603423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300224603.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aEBA_FAO